==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Borough-English
<hw>Bor"ough-Eng"lish</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>A custom, as in some ancient boroughs, by which lands
and tenements descend to the youngest son, instead of the eldest; or, if
the owner have no issue, to the youngest brother.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boroughhead</ent>⟦br⟧
